 ('36', '31', '2', '1', 'en_us', '13', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"About The Paul, Bringer of Doom\",\"slug\":\"about\",\"postDate\":1366095600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":\"1\",\"tags\":[],\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Coder.&nbsp;Wilderness EMT. Geek. Vagabond. Lover of Knowledge. Pursuer of Fun. &nbsp;Attempting to hike the Pacific Crest Trail in 2013.&nbsp;<br><\\/p><p><img src=\\\"http:\\/\\/farm6.staticflickr.com\\/5068\\/5585848234_df184b2a6f_z.jpg\\\" class=\\\"no-center\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><\\/p><p>\\\"Mark well!&nbsp;\\r\\n<br>As Heaven and Earth are fairer, fairer far\\r\\n<br>Than Chaos and blank Darkness, though once chiefs;\\r\\n<br>And as we show beyond that Heaven and Earth\\r\\n<br>In form and shape compact and beautiful,\\r\\n<br>In will, in action free, companionship,\\r\\n<br>And thousand other signs of purer life;\\r\\n<br>So on our heels a fresh perfection treads,\\r\\n<br>A power more strong in beauty, born of us\\r\\n<br>And fated to excel us, as we pass\\r\\n<br>In glory that old Darkness: nor are we\\r\\n<br>Thereby more conquer\'d, than by us the rule\\r\\n<br>Of shapeless Chaos.\\\"\\r\\n<br> - Keats<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>\\\"The human word is neither immortal nor invulnerable; but it is the power that \\r\\n    orders our chaos, and the light by which we live.\\\"\\r\\n    <br>- Northrop Frye<\\/p>\\r\\n\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2013-04-21 01:33:28', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '6e01b548-151c-4710-8787-6ca7a573223c'),
 ('37', '34', '1', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Tuning in from the PCT\",\"slug\":\"tuning-in-from-the-pct\",\"postDate\":1367021999,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":\"1\",\"tags\":[],\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>The hiking is going well but the energy levels at the end of the day for blogging have been non-existent. I am currently sitting underneath the overpass at Scissors Crossing waiting for the sun to sink lower before starting a long climb up out of the valley.&nbsp;Currently 82 here in the shade and slightly above 90 out there in the sun. A bit of wind is providing relief but still pretty darn hot on those sandy slopes. The weather reports is hinting that we might be flirting with upper 90s over the next week.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>Might write more later but if you want a slightly more consistent flow of trip updates follow me on Twitter:&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/reedmaniac\\\">http:\\/\\/twitter.com\\/reedmaniac<\\/a><\\/p>\",\"3\":\"pct\"}}', '2013-04-27 00:19:59', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', 'd72458c0-90f2-47d6-9827-a595dedd61f8'),
