re are a few apps that I recommend you get:<\\/p><ul>\\r\\n\\t<li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/app\\/halfmiles-pct\\/id521937514?mt=8\\\">Halfmile\'s PCT<\\/a><\\/li>\\t<li>Guthook (<a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/app\\/guthooks-pct-southern-california\\/id503652257?mt=8\\\">Southern CA<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/app\\/guthooks-pct-central-california\\/id509016353?mt=8\\\">Central CA<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/app\\/guthooks-pct-northern-california\\/id511715959?mt=8\\\">Northern CA<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/app\\/guthooks-pct-oregon\\/id514159949?mt=8\\\">Oregon<\\/a>, <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/app\\/guthooks-pct-washington\\/id518350895?mt=8\\\">Washington<\\/a>)<\\/li>\\t<li><a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/itunes.apple.com\\/us\\/app\\/pcthyoh\\/id461413265?mt=8\\\">PCTHYOH<\\/a><\\/li><\\/ul><h5>The Halfmile app is based off <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.pctmap.net\\\">Halfmile\'s notes and maps<\\/a>, which is <em>the<\\/em> maps for the Pacific Crest Trail. Using your GPS coordinates, it can tell you where you are on the trail (or how to get back to it) and also the distance to the next Halfmile landmark.  However, after the Sierras, Halfmiles notes are greatly reduced and you will start becoming frustrated when you walk by additional water sources or campsites that are never mentioned.  Guthook\'s apps fills in the blanks with far more water sources (springs!), campsites, and additional details + photos. When you are hiking 20-30 miles a day in all kinds of conditions and terrain, it is helpful to know when the next reliable water source or campsite is around that next bend or 6 miles beyond.  The Guthook app was a bit buggy at times and does not give you any calculated distances, but it was regularly updated while on trail so hopefully it will continue getting better.<\\/h5><p>The <em>PCTHYOH<\\/em> app is simply a nice way to cache information on your phone like PDFs of Halfmile\'s maps. Found it handy a few times when I wanted to look at Halfmile\'s elevation profiles.<\\/p><h4>\\r\\n\\t<strong>POWER!! - <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.amazon.com\\/gp\\/product\\/B004G739C4\\/ref=as_li_ss_tl?tag=reedmaniaccom-20\\\">sCharger-5 High Performance Solar Charger<\\/a> <\\/strong><\\/h4>\",\"3\":\"pct\"}}', '2013-10-09 19:27:09', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '47b0648c-cce0-428a-b900-402134af548e'),
