 ('196', '130', '1', '1', 'en_us', '1', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"The Secret Life of the Thru-Hiker\",\"slug\":\"the-secret-life-of-the-thru-hiker\",\"postDate\":null,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Content<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2013-11-02 21:41:43', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', 'dcc25a99-535f-409f-84e7-a31594d3a470'),
 ('197', '130', '1', '1', 'en_us', '2', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"The Secret Life of the Thru-Hiker\",\"slug\":\"the-secret-life-of-the-thru-hiker\",\"postDate\":1383375600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Content<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2013-11-02 21:41:55', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '82639ff3-b204-46eb-a12f-36cd414f90c2'),
 ('198', '130', '1', '1', 'en_us', '3', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"The Secret Life of the Thru-Hiker\",\"slug\":\"the-secret-life-of-the-thru-hiker\",\"postDate\":1383375600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Returning to civilization has been more of a struggle than I expected.  While thru-hiking, I can only remember a few days when it was a struggle to get out of my sleeping bag in the morning and continue going. Most days that simple, completely focused purpose of continuing North was enough to get me going in the morning.<\\/p><p>Back here in the Real World, it all feels so much more ridiculous and complicated.  There are so many considerations that need to be carefully origami\'ed into my life.  Employment, money, living situation, bills, driving, socializing, rehabilitation of injured parts. Even after being off trail for nearly six weeks, I am still experiencing a low level of anxiety every single day.  It is not a pleasant experience.<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2013-11-05 05:59:17', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '3c23c951-5d2a-4edc-8721-3e2bf3d32900'),
 ('199', '130', '1', '1', 'en_us', '4', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"The Secret Life of the Thru-Hiker\",\"slug\":\"the-secret-life-of-the-thru-hiker\",\"postDate\":1383375600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Returning to civilization has been more of a struggle than I expected.  While thru-hiking, I can only remember a few days when it was a difficult to get out of my sleeping bag in the morning and continue going. Most days that simple, completely focused purpose of continuing North was enough to get me going in the morning.<\\/p><p>Back here in the Real World, it all feels so much more ridiculous and complicated.  There are so many considerations that need to be carefully origami\'ed into my life.  Employment, money, living situation, bills, driving, socializing, rehabilitation of injured parts, what to have for dinner. Even after being off trail for nearly six weeks, I am still experiencing a low level of anxiety every single day.  It is not a pleasant experience.<\\/p><p>I am not exactly fantasizing about being back on the trail either. That trip is over. But, I am thinking about the next trip. The next time that I can get <em>out <strong>there<\\/strong><\\/em>. \\\"Why am I here?\\\" is a constant refrain in my mind.  Why should I not be out there in the forests, deserts, and mountains of the world.  Isn\'t that where I belong?<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2013-11-05 06:03:08', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '005f5123-5511-435e-b975-d7403148b89b'),
