 ('235', '135', '1', '1', 'en_us', '7', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Terrible Inconvenience\",\"slug\":\"a-terrible-inconvenience\",\"postDate\":1398573000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>In the continuing saga of navel gazing because, let us be honest, YouTube is growing a bit stale, we evaluate why I prefer to spend my time on a Saturday night working or writing blog entries instead of heading out for \\\"fun\\\". Self-indulgent,&nbsp;magniloquent,&nbsp;florid prose will undoubtedly make brief appearances in an attempt to&nbsp;disguise any semblance of well-thought out rhetoric. &nbsp;Extra-hyphens and random semicolons may; or may not; help provide humorous interludes from any and all seriousness. &nbsp;Seems like an appropriate time for a second paragraph.<\\/p><p>When did drinking alcohol become the&nbsp;irrepressible&nbsp;mainstay of adult fun? Please, do not get me wrong: I do not&nbsp;<em>dislike<\\/em> alcohol. The sheer scope of varieties and concoctions are a testament to our species\' inherent love of it. &nbsp;Furthermore, I have definitely had a decent fill of it throughout the years. &nbsp;As Amelia can attest, if you put food or drink in front of me, I have a compulsion to consume it; it is in my nature. &nbsp;Separate from that, I do not find it particularly inviting as a daily part of life. &nbsp;I brewed beer solely for the novelty, not for the consumption of its alcohol. I enjoy whisky because it has a certain Scottish allure with a burn at the end that has a manly&nbsp;romanticization from so many Westerns. &nbsp;As for wine, every single time I am offered a glass the health benefits are what usually sway me. &nbsp;Sak\\u00e9 and sangria are the only alcoholic&nbsp;liquids I am ever genuinely tempted by in a store or restaurant when there are not social pressures. &nbsp;Even then, I am far more likely to drink juice or tea.<\\/p><p>Every so often I daydream I have an enzyme that causes alcohol to be less appealing or that certain neurotransmitter receptors are not as beguiled in me as in others. &nbsp;I suspect it is more the fact that I am a bit of a control freak and over the past fifteen years or so I have become less willing to toy with my cerebral cortex and limbic system. &nbsp;I find that on a daily basis, what happens in my noggin is rather sufficient. &nbsp;And, how supposed adults behave under the influence is not even remotely how I wish to behave.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2014-04-27 04:19:51', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '5b71abb9-835a-4e77-a876-3a1fce8bbecf'),
 ('236', '135', '1', '1', 'en_us', '8', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Terrible Inconvenience\",\"slug\":\"a-terrible-inconvenience\",\"postDate\":1398573000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>In the continuing saga of navel gazing because, let us be honest, YouTube is growing a bit stale, we attempt to evaluate why I prefer to spend my Saturday night working or writing blog entries instead of heading out for \\\"fun\\\". Self-indulgent,&nbsp;magniloquent,&nbsp;florid prose will undoubtedly make brief appearances in an attempt to&nbsp;disguise any semblance of well-thought out rhetoric. &nbsp;Extra-hyphens and random semicolons may; or may not; help provide humorous interludes from any and all seriousness. &nbsp;Seems like an appropriate time for a second paragraph.<\\/p><p>When did drinking alcohol become the&nbsp;irrepressible&nbsp;mainstay of adult fun? Please, do not get me wrong: I do not&nbsp;<em>dislike<\\/em> alcohol. The sheer scope of varieties and concoctions are a testament to our species\' inherent love of it. &nbsp;Furthermore, I have definitely had a decent fill of it throughout the years. &nbsp;As Amelia can attest, if you put food or drink in front of me, I have a compulsion to consume it; it is in my nature. &nbsp;Separate from that, I do not find it particularly inviting as a daily part of life. &nbsp;I brewed beer solely for the novelty, not for the consumption of its alcohol. I enjoy whisky because it has a certain Scottish allure with a burn at the end that has a manly&nbsp;romanticization from so many Westerns. &nbsp;As for wine, every single time I am offered a glass the health benefits are what usually sway me. &nbsp;Sak\\u00e9 and sangria are the only alcoholic&nbsp;liquids I am ever genuinely tempted by in a store or restaurant when there are not social pressures. &nbsp;Even then, I am far more likely to drink juice or tea.<\\/p><p>Every so often I daydream I have an enzyme that causes alcohol to be less appealing or that certain neurotransmitter receptors are not as beguiled in me as in others. &nbsp;I suspect it is more the fact that I am a bit of a control freak and over the past fifteen years or so I have become less willing to toy with my cerebral cortex and limbic system. &nbsp;I find that on a daily basis, what happens in my noggin is rather sufficient. &nbsp;And, how supposed adults behave under the influence is not even remotely how I wish to behave.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2014-04-27 04:24:16', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '8ebbe520-1265-4bb4-902f-4f4492cd0ec0'),
 ('237', '135', '1', '1', 'en_us', '9', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Terrible Inconvenience\",\"slug\":\"a-terrible-inconvenience\",\"postDate\":1398573000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>In the continuing saga of navel gazing because, let us be honest, YouTube is growing a bit stale, we attempt to evaluate why I prefer to spend my Saturday night working or writing blog entries instead of heading out for \\\"fun\\\". Self-indulgent,&nbsp;magniloquent,&nbsp;florid prose will undoubtedly make brief appearances as&nbsp;subterfuge&nbsp;for&nbsp;succinct, carefully reasoned rhetoric. Extra-hyphens and random semicolons may; or may not; help provide humorous interludes from any and all seriousness. &nbsp;We now continue onto a second paragraph.<\\/p><p>When did drinking alcohol become the&nbsp;irrepressible&nbsp;mainstay of adult fun? Please, do not get me wrong: I do not&nbsp;<em>dislike<\\/em> alcohol. The sheer scope of varieties and concoctions are a testament to our species\' inherent love of it. &nbsp;Furthermore, I have definitely had a decent fill of it throughout the years. &nbsp;As Amelia can attest, if you put food or drink in front of me, I have a compulsion to consume it; it is in my nature. &nbsp;Separate from that, I do not find it particularly inviting as a daily part of life. &nbsp;I brewed beer solely for the novelty, not for the consumption of its alcohol. I enjoy whisky because it has a certain Scottish allure with a burn at the end that has a manly&nbsp;romanticization from so many Westerns. &nbsp;As for wine, every single time I am offered a glass the health benefits are what usually sway me. &nbsp;Sak\\u00e9 and sangria are the only alcoholic&nbsp;liquids I am ever genuinely tempted by in a store or restaurant when there are not social pressures. &nbsp;Even then, I am far more likely to drink juice or tea.<\\/p><p>Every so often I daydream I have an enzyme that causes alcohol to be less appealing or that certain neurotransmitter receptors are not as beguiled in me as in others. &nbsp;I suspect it is more the fact that I am a bit of a control freak and over the past fifteen years or so I have become less willing to toy with my cerebral cortex and limbic system. &nbsp;I find that on a daily basis, what happens in my noggin is rather sufficient. &nbsp;And, how supposed adults behave under the influence is not even remotely how I wish to behave.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2014-04-27 04:30:10', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '151c5ff3-7307-4991-95cc-4258cccac8b7'),
 ('238', '135', '1', '1', 'en_us', '10', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"A Terrible Inconvenience\",\"slug\":\"a-terrible-inconvenience\",\"postDate\":1398573000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>2In the continuing saga of navel gazing because, let us be honest, YouTube is growing a bit stale, we attempt to evaluate why I prefer to spend my Saturday night working or writing blog entries instead of heading out for \\\"fun\\\". Self-indulgent,&nbsp;magniloquent,&nbsp;florid prose will undoubtedly make brief appearances as&nbsp;subterfuge&nbsp;for&nbsp;succinct, carefully reasoned rhetoric. Extra-hyphens and random semicolons may; or may not; help provide humorous interludes from any and all seriousness. &nbsp;We now continue onto a second paragraph.<\\/p><p>When did drinking alcohol become the&nbsp;irrepressible&nbsp;mainstay of adult fun? Please, do not get me wrong: I do not&nbsp;<em>dislike<\\/em> alcohol. The sheer scope of varieties and concoctions are a testament to our species\' inherent love of it. &nbsp;Furthermore, I have definitely had a decent fill of it throughout the years. &nbsp;As Amelia can attest, if you put food or drink in front of me, I have a compulsion to consume it; it is in my nature. &nbsp;Separate from that, I do not find it particularly inviting as a daily part of life. &nbsp;I brewed beer solely for the novelty, not for the consumption of its alcohol. I enjoy whisky because it has a certain Scottish allure with a burn at the end that has a manly&nbsp;romanticization from so many Westerns. &nbsp;As for wine, every single time I am offered a glass the health benefits are what usually sway me. &nbsp;Sak\\u00e9 and sangria are the only alcoholic&nbsp;liquids I am ever genuinely tempted by in a store or restaurant when there are not social pressures. &nbsp;Even then, I am far more likely to drink juice or tea.<\\/p><p>Every so often I daydream I have an enzyme that causes alcohol to be less appealing or that certain neurotransmitter receptors are not as beguiled in me as in others. &nbsp;I suspect it is more the fact that I am a bit of a control freak and over the past fifteen years or so I have become less willing to toy with my cerebral cortex and limbic system. &nbsp;I find that on a daily basis, what happens in my noggin is rather sufficient. Do not feel much of a drive to be&nbsp;more talkative, more self-confident, or less socially inhibited. Surely do not feel like my emotions need more free rein,&nbsp;especially publicly. My judgment and thinking are perfectly muddled enough, thank you very much, and I surely do not need to be more reckless in my activities.<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2014-04-27 04:38:29', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '801a5bdf-aa48-4b98-8031-4e013da6ef28'),
