 ('277', '142', '1', '1', 'en_us', '5', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"River of Lethe\",\"slug\":\"river-of-lethe\",\"postDate\":1413138600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>A bumper crop of engagements and weddings appeared this year, providing a rather steady stream of pokes from the stick of singlehood. Gentle reminders that many friends are buying houses, taking engagement photos, going on long vacations, and settling down with a loved one or well providing manservant.<\\/p><p>Since I have been determined to stay in one place this year and eliminate a significant portion of the financial drain of my student loans, I have made multiple attempts at genuinely meeting someone.<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"pct\"}}', '2014-10-12 18:47:45', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '21c53486-26d6-4331-b5fe-28449fe03e38'),
 ('278', '142', '1', '1', 'en_us', '6', NULL, '{\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"River of Lethe\",\"slug\":\"river-of-lethe\",\"postDate\":1413138600,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>A bumper crop of engagements and weddings appeared this year, providing a rather steady stream of pokes from the stick of singlehood. Gentle reminders that many friends are buying houses, taking engagement photos, going on long vacations, and settling down with a loved one or well providing manservant.<\\/p><p>Since I have been resolved to stay in one place this year and eliminate a significant portion of the financial drain provided by my student loans, I have also, from time to time, endeavoured to pursue opportunities where a relationship might conceivably occur. &nbsp;The usual vectors have been investigated: socializing in new situations,&nbsp;investigating online dating, and when leaving the house actually engaging with people and not shuttering myself in my own thoughts.<\\/p><p>In the end, I think the only conclusion one can rightly draw is that Dating Sucks. &nbsp;Perhaps it is my typically analytical approach to life, but if this was a scientific experiment, one would definitely question if it is the right approach to the problem. And yet, other people seem to pull it off. &nbsp;I mean, how do they do it? I do not understand!<\\/p><p>Online dating seemed rather promising at first. Set out criteria, answer questions and rate them on importance, and then find matches in your area. &nbsp;You have conveniently eliminated the most difficult part of in-person interactions: are they single and are they interested. &nbsp;And yet, wow, can you not rely on their algorithms at all when it comes to in-person chemistry.<\\/p><p>In-person interactions have the old are they single and are they interested, and then it seems I have terrible luck in attracting people my age.<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"pct\"}}', '2014-10-12 19:08:57', '2015-01-17 19:43:04', '1a5acc69-8ceb-4b39-84d9-36