 ('354', '165', '1', '1', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Best of Times, Worst of Times\",\"slug\":\"best-of-times-worst-of-times\",\"postDate\":1433660400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>There is a truth found in darkness. Despite all the words society tends to negatively ascribe to the dark\\u2013veiled, cloaked, shadowed\\u2013what it does allow is isolation and focus. Those whispers in your mind that you can ignore when the sun is shining gain power as you journey further into night.  You are never more alone with your own thoughts than at night while waiting for dawn.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br>\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br>\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2015-06-08 06:38:20', '2015-06-08 06:38:20', '59e2e38a-0a33-4ae5-bfb1-7d0ae1a3e676'),
 ('355', '165', '1', '1', 'en_us', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Best of Times, Worst of Times\",\"slug\":\"best-of-times-worst-of-times\",\"postDate\":1433660400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>I am not one to raise my voice in frustration or anger.  Neither do I ignore responsibilities or easily lose the ability to focus. I will push myself to extraordinary lengths to pull off a worthy goal.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Sleep? Plenty of time to sleep when you die.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>Not possible? We\'ll find a way.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>I will burn my mind to a crisp and run my body into the ground. It is an exceptional moment when I look at a situation and declare it hopeless. Giving up is not what I do.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>However, as much as I love the idea of doom, I want challenges not inevitable failures. Eventually you have to realistically look at a situation and figure out if it is worth it. And for work, it finally reached the point where I was Done, capital D. There was nothing left for me to do. The situation had gotten so stressful, so exhausting, so frustratingly out of my control that my mind decreed all work would cease immediately.\\r\\n<\\/p><p>I kid you not, that is more or less how it happened.  After months and months of 50+ hour work weeks, having other individuals circumvent the product development process repeatedly, and the extra pressure of training two new employees...a proverbial straw was placed upon my back and my mind broke. It refused to do anything further. No amount of rest, caffeine, or convincing could get it to even look at the screen a moment longer.  I turned in my resignation 24 hours later.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br>\\r\\n<\\/p>\",\"3\":\"personal\"}}', '2015-06-08 07:40:02', '2015-06-08 07:40:02', 'be7377c6-cf86-4f03-b4ff-9ca57d7cf49a'),
