 ('413', '184', '1', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Where Do We Go From Here?\",\"slug\":\"where-do-we-go-from-here\",\"postDate\":1438585200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Been an interesting few days here at the Lohrenz Shelter for Displayed Youths - Anacortes branch. Ideas are being discussed, links shared, and decisions slowly being made.  Now, plans are slowly being mapped out.<\\/p><p>One of the pillars on which Amelia and I\'s long-term friendship is based is the mutual persistence of the \\\"Why am I here?\\\" question.  There is a very real and powerful part of our minds that are always evaluating the present situation and prepared to leave. We know how disquieting this can be for employers and potential partners alike, but at this point it is etched into our beings. Not that we vamoose whenever the urge takes us, mind you. Typically there is a long runway of thought and consultation prior to moving on; and any delay may have a deeper cause than the ostensible reason too.<\\/p><p>On my side, in the past few years, despite considerable expenditures of time and energy towards \\\"productive\\\" goals, I ebbed towards a serve disappointment regarding the stereotypically American adulthood habits.  To take the metaphor too far: I found myself with the tide out, stuck in muck, and slightly offended by the smell.<\\/p>\"}}', '2015-08-03 23:03:32', '2015-08-03 23:03:32', 'db6786d5-0a2d-4c99-82c6-7c837126d90e'),
 ('414', '184', '1', '1', 'en_us', '4', '', '{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Where Do We Go From Here?\",\"slug\":\"where-do-we-go-from-here\",\"postDate\":1438585200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Been an interesting few days here at the Lohrenz Shelter for Displayed Youths - Anacortes branch. Ideas are being discussed, links shared, and decisions slowly being made.  Now, plans are slowly being mapped out.<\\/p><p>One of the pillars on which Amelia and I\'s long-term friendship is based is the mutual persistence of the \\\"Why am I here?\\\" question.  There is a very real and powerful part of our minds that are always evaluating the present situation and prepared to leave. We know how disquieting this can be for employers and potential partners alike, but at this point it is etched into our beings. Not that we vamoose whenever the urge takes us, mind you. Typically there is a long runway of thought and consultation prior to moving on; and any delay may have a deeper cause than the ostensible reason too.<\\/p><p>On my side, in the past few years, despite considerable expenditures of time and energy towards \\\"productive\\\" goals, I ebbed towards a serve disappointment regarding the stereotypically American adulthood habits.  To take the metaphor too far: I found myself with the tide out, stuck in muck, and slightly offended by the smell.  Sure, I could attribute this attitude about the state of my life, the nation, and the world to my perfectionist, idealistic, well educated, hoytie toytie intellectualism about reality...but come on...really?<\\/p><ul><li>How does a country desperate for doctors, still have no way to alleviate the cost of medical school?<\\/li><li>How does a startup company pay two of its employees as much as the rest combined?<\\/li><li>How the bloody hell is <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.washingtontimes.com\\/news\\/2015\\/jul\\/31\\/obama-signs-short-term-highway-bill\\/\\\">Congress not funding infrastructure<\\/a>?<\\/li><li>Why does it a <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bloomberg.com\\/news\\/articles\\/2015-07-30\\/warren-buffett-s-family-secretly-funded-a-birth-control-revolution\\\">take a billionaire<\\/a> to get sensical birth control funded?<\\/li><\\/ul><p><br><\\/p>\"}}', '2015-08-03 23:18:32', '2015-08-03 23:18:32', '2e8d20fb-7073-4142-816b-3a040d31d3b5'),
 ('415', '184', '1', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Where Do We Go From Here?\",\"slug\":\"where-do-we-go-from-here\",\"postDate\":1438585200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Been an interesting few days here at the<em> Lohrenz Shelter for Displayed Youths - Anacortes branch<\\/em>. Ideas are being discussed, links shared, and decisions slowly being made.  Now, plans are slowly being mapped out.<\\/p><p>One of the pillars on which Amelia and I\'s long-term friendship is based is the mutual persistence of the \\\"Why am I here?\\\" question.  There is a very real and powerful part of our minds that are always evaluating the present situation and prepared to leave. We know how disquieting this can be for employers and potential partners alike, but at this point it is etched into our beings. Not that we vamoose whenever the urge takes us, mind you. Typically there is a long runway of thought and consultation prior to moving on; and any delay may have a deeper cause than the ostensible reason too.<\\/p><p>On my side, in the past few years, despite considerable expenditures of time and energy towards \\\"productive\\\" goals, I ebbed towards a serve disappointment regarding the stereotypically American adulthood habits.  To take the metaphor too far: I found myself with the tide out, stuck in muck, and slightly offended by the smell.  Sure, I could attribute this attitude about the state of my life, the nation, and the world to my perfectionist, idealistic, perhaps overly educated, hoytie toytie views about reality...but come on...really?<\\/p><p>I could probably list off a few of the major things bugging me (today) like the the cost of medical school (and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bloomberg.com\\/bw\\/articles\\/2013-04-04\\/why-your-student-loan-interest-rate-is-so-high\\\">high student loan rates<\\/a> and debt), how it <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bloomberg.com\\/news\\/articles\\/2015-07-30\\/warren-buffett-s-family-secretly-funded-a-birth-control-revolution\\\">took a billionaire<\\/a> to get sensical birth control funded, that Congress is so incompetent that we cannot get <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.washingtontimes.com\\/news\\/2015\\/jul\\/31\\/obama-signs-short-term-highway-bill\\/\\\">infrastructure funded<\\/a>, that our entire National Park system is <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.npca.org\\/protecting-our-parks\\/park-funding\\/park-funding.html\\\">likely to be gutted yet again<\\/a> by Congress right before its centennial, and the sin-against-common-decency known as auto-play videos.<\\/p><p>I think in the end is that I work exceptionally hard to learn, work, stay informed, communicate with my Representatives, and be a fair minded person.  And then, at the end of the day, only the bare minimal of what I believe should happen actually happens. It is very discouraging. <\\/p>\"}}', '2015-08-03 23:41:29', '2015-08-03 23:41:29', 'e8288bf3-81a3-44b3-9fe0-6d9e7eb1f962'),
 ('416', '184', '1', '1', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Where Do We Go From Here?\",\"slug\":\"where-do-we-go-from-here\",\"postDate\":1438639200,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>Been an interesting few days here at the<em> Lohrenz Shelter for Displayed Youths - Anacortes branch<\\/em>. Ideas are being discussed, links shared, and decisions slowly being made.  Now, plans are slowly being mapped out.<\\/p><p>One of the pillars on which Amelia and I\'s long-term friendship is based is the mutual persistence of the \\\"Why am I here?\\\" and \\\"What am I doing here?\\\" questions.  There is a very real and powerful part of our minds that are always evaluating the present situation and prepared to leave. We know how disquieting this can be for employers and potential partners alike, but at this point it is etched into our beings. Not that we vamoose whenever the urge takes us, mind you. Typically there is a long runway of thought and consultation prior to moving on; and any delay may have a deeper cause than the ostensible reason too.<\\/p><p>On my side, in the past few years, despite considerable expenditures of time and energy towards \\\"productive\\\" goals, I ebbed towards a serve disappointment regarding the stereotypically American adulthood habits.  To take the metaphor too far: I found myself with the tide out, stuck in muck, and slightly offended by the smell.  Sure, I could attribute this attitude about the state of my life, the nation, and the world to my perfectionist, idealistic, perhaps overly educated, hoytie toytie views about reality...but come on...really?<\\/p><p>I could probably list off a few of the major things bugging me (today) like the the cost of medical school (and <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bloomberg.com\\/bw\\/articles\\/2013-04-04\\/why-your-student-loan-interest-rate-is-so-high\\\">high student loan rates<\\/a> and debt), how it <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.bloomberg.com\\/news\\/articles\\/2015-07-30\\/warren-buffett-s-family-secretly-funded-a-birth-control-revolution\\\">took a billionaire<\\/a> to get sensical birth control funded, that Congress is so incompetent that we cannot get <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.washingtontimes.com\\/news\\/2015\\/jul\\/31\\/obama-signs-short-term-highway-bill\\/\\\">infrastructure funded<\\/a>, that our entire National Park system is <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.npca.org\\/protecting-our-parks\\/park-funding\\/park-funding.html\\\">likely to be gutted yet again<\\/a> by Congress right before its centennial, the sin-against-common-decency known as auto-play videos, and how warped compensation and decisions were at my last job.<\\/p><p>I toil exceptionally hard to learn, work, stay informed, pay taxes, communicate with my Representatives, and be a fair minded person about other viewpoints.  And then, at the end of the day, only the bare minimal of what I believe should happen actually happens. It is very discouraging. <\\/p><p>Part of me wants to do the stomping around routine and shout \\\"HOW IS THIS OK?!\\\" Another part reminds me that I have known for quite a while that money and power are where real influence is and I have the abilities to acquire both. And then, well, then part of me just wants to escape. The human adult world is not meeting my expectations. It\'s fired.<\\/p><p>So, I think I am headed to Alaska next.<\\/p>\"}}', '2015-08-03 23:53:43', '2015-08-03 23:53:43', 'a02c85da-35d4-4be3-88d0-ee759c2dcd14'),
