 of the tourist buses there for $10 as I did not realize it only went to the Visitor Center and the Mendenhall Lake Campground was on the other side of the lake, over an hour\'s walk away.  While walking a cab came near and I hailed it down.  For $12, I skipped a 90 minute walk and was dropped off right at the West Glacier Trail trailhead.  The hike up was relatively easy and at 3.4 miles in a quick scramble brought you to a nice overlook where I got a <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.flickr.com\\/photos\\/133323973@N07\\/20673078958\\/in\\/album-72157657725794351\\/\\\">few beautiful panoramas<\\/a>.  Hiking back down, I took an unmaintained, mildly rugged offshoot trail and headed down to the foot of the glacier to view the moraine and peek into a few ice caves. The weather and glacier were superb and I felt incredibly lucky to have an entire day of clear weather to explore it. <\\/p><p style=\\\"margin-left: 40px;\\\">That evening one of the hostel guests showed me some of her photos from her whale watching tour that day. A group of humpbacks had been bubble net feeding in the area for days and it was truly a sight to see.  Unfortunately, the next morning I discovered the whale tour I had wanted to get one had been canceled because of cruise ships leaving early or changing their tour schedules. Backpackers are a very very small minority of the visitors in SE Alaska and the cruise ships really do run the show. With no other plans, I consulted my handy Lonely Planet guide and learned of the Taku Glacier and Taku Lodge seaplane tour.  Within an hour I was in a plane and flying towards Taku Glacier for a scenic tour of the nearby icefield and a king salmon dinner at the lodge.  And it just so happened that a black bear showed up to clear the <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.flickr.com\\/photos\\/133323973@N07\\/20673100940\\/in\\/album-72157657725794351\\/\\\">drippings off of the grill<\\/a>.  While the tour was definitely a bit pricey, I have never had such amazing views of a glacier <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.flickr.com\\/photos\\/133323973@N07\\/20240159833\\/in\\/album-72157657725794351\\/\\\">from the air<\\/a> and the <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.flickr.com\\/photos\\/133323973@N07\\/20834871976\\/in\\/album-72157657725794351\\/\\\">meal was delicious<\\/a>.<\\/p>\"}}', '2015-09-20 18:00:48', '2015-09-20 18:00:48', 'fe02c6b3-d8d9-4440-9ffb-4008b4e70b01'),
