 ('514', '223', '1', '1', 'en_us', '9', '', '{\"typeId\":\"1\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"2016 Activity Log \\u2013 An Attempt at Structure\",\"slug\":\"2016-activity-log\",\"postDate\":1460244360,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":0,\"fields\":{\"1\":\"<p>As an active, outdoorsy, geeky, and nerdy individual who gobbles up medical studies and gear reviews nearly every single day, I have oddly never made a real record of my athletic activities. Off and on I have dabbled with the <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.mapmyfitness.com\\\">MapMyFitness<\\/a> sites to help figure out how far I ran or what the elevation profile was for a bike ride, but not with any true serious intention to keep it up to date or analyze the data later. In my own way I was being a purist to my belief that the activity itself is the worthier part than any sort of personal record or achievement. My little stab at applying Kantian moral philosophy to athletics.  Gods, I just typed that out and rolled my own eyes at it.  ::slow applause::<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><p><br><\\/p><iframe id=\\\"pageswitcher-content\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" marginheight=\\\"0\\\" marginwidth=\\\"0\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/spreadsheets\\/d\\/1ss-h-AqmCKR57EpAr66E6jVs_9YyvwE4_M_LebdLf_8\\/pubhtml?gid=509608816&single=false&widget=true&headers=false\\\" style=\\\"display: block; width: 100%; height: 500px;\\\">&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;span id=\\\"selection-marker-1\\\" class=\\\"redactor-selection-marker\\\" data-verified=\\\"redactor\\\"&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;lt;\\/span&amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;amp;gt;\\r\\n<\\/iframe>\"}}', '2016-04-10 02:28:45', '2016-04-10 02:28:45', '4d4826c8-693a-4801-bb31-e4e12acc07c5'),
