tting issues.  Not a huge fan of Google Drive but if I am going to share this data with others, I may have to switch to using it for the daily updates too.  Bugger.\\r\\n<\\/p><p><br><\\/p><iframe id=\\\"pageswitcher-content\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" marginheight=\\\"0\\\" marginwidth=\\\"0\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/docs.google.com\\/spreadsheets\\/d\\/1ss-h-AqmCKR57EpAr66E6jVs_9YyvwE4_M_LebdLf_8\\/pubhtml?gid=509608816&single=false&widget=true&headers=false\\\" style=\\\"display: block; width: 100%; height: 500px;\\\">\\r\\n<\\/iframe><p><br><\\/p><p>After I made the Compiled sheet with all the totals in one table, I noticed a pretty substantial data oversight.  While I am keeping track of time for activities like running, biking and weights, I am completely skipping it for things like swimming, snowshoeing, and alpine touring. Swimming is reasonably calculable thanks to me being pretty consistent at a 30 minute mile at the moment. Alpine touring and snowshoeing, though, would have to be educated guesses based on my remembrance of the day and any photos I took during the activity. Back of the napkin workings have me missing about 35 hours worth of time.<\\/p><p>So, after 14 weeks, what do I see here? Apparently, I am averaging about 9.3 hours of exercise per week.   If you consider that I normally take two rest days per week and took an entire week off at the beginning of March, that means on days I exercise, I am average  two hours of activity. Not too shabby.<\\/p><p>Comparing February and March, it is quite apparent that I slashed my running in order to start swimming again and also go biking, hiking, and alpine touring.  What is not immediately apparent is that the shorter runs I did in March were done a bit faster, resulting in me pulling off an 8:30\\/mile pace during a trail run today, which is a minute faster than my average time in February.  A calculated field might be required for that.<\\/p><p>One rather embarrassing statistic is my time spent stretching. 460 minutes in January, 295 minutes in February, but only 85 minutes in March. Not a good trend. Need to work on that in April.<\\/p><p>Is it worth having this information? I suppose it really depends on my aims for all of this activity.  I call it training but I am not really training for anything in particular.  I would not mind finally running all of Wildwood in one go and I have a dream of climbing both Mt. Hood and Mt. Adams in one day too. <\\/p>\"}}', '2016-04-10 03:30:51', '2016-04-10 03:30:51', 'cd2d4a61-f9bd-494c-9ace-2d6070ea343e'),
